---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Clipboard Copy Button
description: a button that copies text to the clipboard
---

{% from "components/clipboard-copy-button/macro.njk" import clipboardCopyButton %}
{% from "components/united-kingdom-national-health-service-number-view/macro.njk" import unitedKingdomNationalHealthServiceNumberView %}

<h2>Copy literal text</h2>
<p>
  Your NHS number:
  {{ unitedKingdomNationalHealthServiceNumberView({ value: "4857773456" }) }}
  {{ clipboardCopyButton({
    text: "Copy",
    clipboardText: "4857773456",
    label: "Copy NHS number to clipboard"
  }) }}
</p>

<h2>Copy from another element</h2>
<p>
  <code id="booking-code" class="code">B-2026-0042</code>
  {{ clipboardCopyButton({
    text: "Copy booking code",
    target: "#booking-code",
    label: "Copy booking code to clipboard"
  }) }}
</p>

<h2>Progressive enhancement</h2>
<p>The macro emits <code>data-module="clipboard-copy-button"</code>
  so a JavaScript module can hook up <code>navigator.clipboard</code>
  and announce success to a nearby live region. The button is
  still valid markup without JS; consumers decide whether to hide
  it or show a fallback copy target when enhancement fails.</p>
